body:
@ijuma 
_**failOnVersionConflict()**_ leaves pretty much no choice: you either force/fix **all** dependencies or your build fails (yes, it may look like an overkill). 
Keep in mind that this solution also brings one important advantage: **any** future similar issue with redundant dependencies (different versions) will be prevented instantly (i.e. build will fail and hence another force rule should/must be added).

Of course, we can always settle with option **_2._** and fix only this specific problem with **jackson-annotations**:
```
    configurations {
        runtime {
            resolutionStrategy {
                force "com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-annotations:$versions.jackson"
            }
        }
    }
```
What do you prefer ?
